'''Conference of Western Balkan States''' is a 28 August 2014 conference of heads of states and governments of [[Western Balkans]] region initiated by [[German chancellor]] [[Angela Merkel]]. Idea for organization of conference came in light of the celebration of the 100th anniversary of the beginning of [[World War I]].<ref name="DW-BBX" /> It is the first conference in this framework and organizers expressed their desire to continue it in future with [[Wienna]] and [[Paris]] mentioned as a potential next hosts after [[Berlin]].<ref name="Glas Srpske">{{cite web |url=http://www.glassrpske.com/novosti/vijesti_dana/Sastanak-u-Berlinu-temelj-za-sirenje-Evrope/161417.html|title=<U+0421><U+0430><U+0441><U+0442><U+0430><U+043D><U+0430><U+043A> <U+0443> <U+0411><U+0435><U+0440><U+043B><U+0438><U+043D><U+0443> <U+0442><U+0435><U+043C><U+0435><U+0459> <U+0437><U+0430> <U+0448><U+0438><U+0440><U+0435><U+045A><U+0435> <U+0415><U+0432><U+0440><U+043E><U+043F><U+0435>|accessdate=27 August 2014 |author=[[Glas Srpske]]|language=[[Serbian language|Serbian]]}}</ref> [[G<U+00FC>nther Oettinger]] confirmed at conference that event will be organised annually with [[Wienna]] as a host city in 2015 and [[Paris]] in 2016.<ref name="DW-ParizLondonLisabon">{{cite web |url=http://www.dw.de/nova-dinamika-evrointegracija/a-17886877|title=Nova dinamika evrointegracija|accessdate=28 August 2014 |author=[[Deutsche Welle]]|language=[[Serbian language|Serbian]]}}</ref>

The German chancellor announced intention to organize a conference on 7 June 2014.<ref name="Fondation EurActiv PoliTech">{{cite web |url=http://www.euractiv.com/sections/enlargement/merkel-organise-western-balkans-conference-august-302778|title=Merkel to organise Western Balkans conference in August|accessdate=27 August 2014 |author=Fondation EurActiv PoliTech}}</ref> Invitation for participation was sent to all the countries of [[South Eastern Europe]] including [[Croatia]] and [[Slovenia]] that were already members of the [[European Union]] at the time of conference.<ref name="Fondation EurActiv PoliTech" />

The main intention was to show commitment for process of [[Future enlargement of the European Union]], little progress of [[Accession of Bosnia and Herzegovina to the European Union|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] and [[Accession of Macedonia to the European Union|Macedonia]] in that process and relations of [[Serbia]] as a main strategic partner of the EU in region with [[Russia]] in the light of [[International sanctions during the 2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]].<ref name="Fondation EurActiv PoliTech" />

During the Foreign Ministers<U+2019> segment, Albanian Foreign Minister Bushati underlined the importance of making this initiative periodical, as well as finding the right instruments to enable, in future years, the drafting and implementation of concrete joint projects in the region. In this regard Albanian delegation presented a document under the title <U+201C>Albanian Working Paper for the Western Balkans Conference in Berlin<U+201D>, which is based in the vision of <U+201C>a region in peace and well prepared to join the European Union, by guarantying a dignified living for all its citizens."
<ref>http://www.punetejashtme.gov.al/en/press-office/news/minister-bushati-attends-western-balkans-summit-in-berlin&page=1</ref>

At conference was announced future visit of [[Prime Minister of Albania|Albanian Prime Minister]] [[Edi Rama]] to [[Serbia]]. It will be the first meeting of this type between two countries after 1947 meeting of [[Enver Hoxha]] with [[President of Yugoslavia]] [[Josip Broz Tito]].<ref name="ALB-SRB">{{cite web |url=http://www.rts.rs/page/stories/ci/story/1/%D0%9F%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%B0/1683556/%D0%9F%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%B8%D1%87%D0%BA%D0%B0+%D0%B8+%D0%B5%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%BC%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B0+%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%B1%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BD%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82+%D0%BA%D1%99%D1%83%D1%87%D0%BD%D0%B8.html|title=<U+041D><U+0435><U+045B><U+0435><U+043C><U+043E> <U+0431><U+0438><U+0442><U+0438> <U+0438><U+0437><U+043C><U+0435><U+0452><U+0443> <U+0447><U+0435><U+043A><U+0438><U+045B><U+0430> <U+0438> <U+043D><U+0430><U+043A><U+043E><U+0432><U+045A><U+0430>|accessdate=28 August 2014 |author=[[Radio Television of Serbia]]|language=[[Serbian language|Serbian]]}}</ref>

[[Franz Lothar Altmann]], expert on the Balkans,<ref name="Altmann, Franz-Lothar">{{cite web |url=http://www.eurotopics.net/en/home/autorenindex/autor_altmann_franz_lothar/|title=Altmann, Franz-Lothar|accessdate=27 August 2014 |author=[[Eurotopics]]}}</ref> stated in his pre-conference interview for [[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]] that conference proves increasing importance of Balkan region, especially with respect to [[Ukraine crisis]].<ref name="Free Europe">{{cite web |url=http://www.slobodnaevropa.org/content/altman-raste-vaznost-balkana-zbog-ukrajinske-krize/26549749.html|title=Altman: Raste va<U+017E>nost Balkana zbog ukrajinske krize|accessdate=27 August 2014 |author=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|language=[[Serbian language|Serbian]]}}</ref>

==Regional activities before conference==

Prime ministers of Serbia [[Aleksandar Vu<U+010D>i<U+0107>]] and Deputy Chair of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Council of Ministers of Bosnia [[Zlatko Lagumd<U+017E>ija]] met in [[Belgrade]] on 20 of August to agree on joint projects that two countries will present in Berlin.<ref name="B92 Serbia-Bosnia">{{cite web |url=http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics.php?yyyy=2014&mm=08&dd=20&nav_id=91354|title=Serbia, Bosnia to have joint projects in Berlin|accessdate=27 August 2014 |author=[[B92]]}}</ref> Serbian delegation also announced its intention seek support for infrastructure projectof modernization of the [[Belgrade<U+2013>Bar railway]].<ref name="B92" />

On 25 of August 2014 Prime ministers of Croatia, Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina, and Albania meet prior to conference in Croatian town of [[Cavtat]].<ref name="Government of Montenegro" /> Prime ministers exchange views on infrastructure projects and other topics of common interest which may be discussed at conference.<ref name="Government of Montenegro" />

[[Croatia]] announced its intention to seek support for construction of section of [[Adriatic<U+2013>Ionian motorway]] along the coast conditional on it receiving EU funds for the [[Pelje<U+0161>ac Bridge]].<ref name="Croatia insisting on pointless bridge">{{cite web |url=http://www.eurotopics.net/en/home/presseschau/archiv/article/ARTICLE149337-Croatia-insisting-on-pointless-bridge|title=Croatia insisting on pointless bridge|accessdate=27 August 2014 |author=[[Eurotopics]]}}</ref>

On 2014 [[Croatia Summit]] Aleksei Meshkov, Russian Deputy Foreign Minister, said that European Union should not push the Western Balkan States to select EU or Russia.<ref name="HRT Dubrovnik">{{cite web |url=http://vijesti.hrt.hr/rusija-eu-ne-smije-pritiskati-zapadni-balkan-izborom-eu-ili-rusija|title=Rusija: EU ne smije pritiskati zapadni Balkan izborom EU ili Rusija|accessdate=27 August 2014 |author=[[Croatian Radio Television]]|language=[[Croatian language|Croatian]]}}</ref>

